abstract: The Franco-Swiss filmmaker and provocateur radically rethought motion pictures and left a lasting influence on the medium.
snippet: The Franco-Swiss filmmaker and provocateur radically rethought motion pictures and left a lasting influence on the medium.
lead_paragraph: Jean-Luc Godard, the daringly innovative director and provocateur whose unconventional camera work, disjointed narrative style and penchant for radical politics changed the course of filmmaking in the 1960s, leaving a lasting influence on it, died on Tuesday at his home in Rolle, Switzerland. He was 91.

main: Jean-Luc Godard, 91, Is Dead; Bold Director Shaped French New Wave
print_headline: Jean-Luc Godard, Master of French New Wave, Is Dead at 91

main: In Nord Stream Mystery, Baltic Seabed Provides a Nearly Ideal Crime Scene
print_headline: A Pipeline Mystery in the Baltic, With a Seabed Ripe for Sabotage

abstract: Impose sanctions on the wealth managers who create these complex offshore shell games.
snippet: Impose sanctions on the wealth managers who create these complex offshore shell games.
lead_paragraph: Russian oligarchs were hit with sanctions last year in an effort to cut off Vladimir Putins overseas lieutenants from their vast offshore wealth  an estimated 60 percent of their net worth. Mega-yachts, private jets and luxury villas were seized, sometimes with news cameras rolling. Yet for all that drama, much of the oligarchs money was quietly moved to safer havens.

main: Break the Chain Between Russian Oligarchs and Managers, and You Break Everything
print_headline: When Oligarchs Dodge Sanctions, Target Their Money Managers

abstract: Russia has accused the country of harboring a Ukrainian woman it blames for a fatal car bombing over the weekend.
snippet: Russia has accused the country of harboring a Ukrainian woman it blames for a fatal car bombing over the weekend.
lead_paragraph: Estonia, accused by Russia of harboring a Ukrainian woman whom Moscow has blamed for a fatal car bombing over the weekend, said on Monday that it had received no official request for information or cooperation from Moscow in connection with the attack, which killed Daria Dugina, a Russian commentator and the daughter of a prominent ultranationalist.

main: Estonia says Moscow has not asked for help with the Dugina investigation.

abstract: Average life expectancy has risen by 16 years since the national retirement age was set at 65. We asked health experts when they think people should stop working now.
snippet: Average life expectancy has risen by 16 years since the national retirement age was set at 65. We asked health experts when they think people should stop working now.
lead_paragraph: In 1881, the conservative German Chancellor Otto von Bismarck, plagued by a rise in socialist ideology, proposed a national retirement benefit to appease the leftist masses. He set the retirement age at 70. Average life expectancy at the time? About 40 years.

main: What Is the Ideal Retirement Age for Your Health?
